name: additional_properties
description: A JSON string containing any payload properties not present in the schema

name: document_id
description: The document ID specified in the URI when the client sent this message

fields.name: app_disabled
fields.description: True if this add-on cannot be used in the application based on version compatibility, dependencies, and blocklisting. This field is only available after the 'sessionstore-windows-restored' topic is notified.

fields.name: blocklisted
fields.description: Whether or not the add-on appears in the blocklist. This field is only available after the 'sessionstore-windows-restored' topic is notified.

fields.name: has_binary_components
fields.description: True or false depending on whether the add-on has binary components. This is always false since Firefox 60. This field is only available after the 'sessionstore-windows-restored' topic is notified.

fields.name: install_day
fields.description: The days since epoch that the add-on was first installed. This field is only available after the 'sessionstore-windows-restored' topic is notified.

fields.name: is_system
fields.description: Whether or not the add-on is a system add-on. This field is available at startup.

fields.name: name
fields.description: The add-on name, limited to 100 characters. This field is only available after the 'sessionstore-windows-restored' topic is notified.

fields.name: scope
fields.description: Indicates what scope the add-on is installed in, per profile, user, system, or application. This field is available at startup.

fields.name: signed_state
fields.description: The state of the signature of the add-on. This field is only available after the 'sessionstore-windows-restored' topic is notified.

fields.name: update_day
fields.description: The day the add-on was last updated. This field is optional, but available at startup if present.

fields.name: is_web_extension
fields.description: Whether or not the add-on is a WebExtension add-on. This field is available at startup.

fields.name: multiprocess_compatible
fields.description: Whether or not the add-on is a compatible with e10s. Since Firefox 61, this is always true. This field is available at startup.

fields.name: architecture
fields.description: The build architecture for the active build.

fields.name: build_id
fields.description: The build ID/date of the application.

fields.name: version
fields.description: The version of the application.

fields.name: distribution_id
fields.description: The value of the `distribution.id` pref that identifies the Firefox distribution.

fields.name: creation_date
fields.description: The creation date of the user profile as the integer number of days since UNIX epoch.

fields.name: addon_compatibility_check_enabled
fields.description: Whether application compatibility is respected for add-ons.

fields.name: campaign
fields.description: Identifier of the particular campaign that led to the download of the product.

fields.name: content
fields.description: Identifier to indicate the particular link within a campaign.

fields.name: medium
fields.description: Category of the source, such as 'organic' for a search engine.

fields.name: source
fields.description: Referring partner domain, when install happens via a known partner.

fields.name: blocklist_enabled
fields.description: True if the blocklist is enabled.

fields.name: default_search_engine
fields.description: Contains the string identifier or name of the default search engine provider. Deprecated.

fields.name: load_path
fields.description: The anonymized path of the engine xml file, e.g. e.g. jar:[app]/omni.ja!browser/engine.xml (where ‘browser’ is the name of the chrome package, not a folder) [profile]/searchplugins/engine.xml [distribution]/searchplugins/common/engine.xml [other]/engine.xml [other]/addEngineWithDetails [other]/addEngineWithDetails:extensionID [http/https]example.com/engine-name.xml [http/https]example.com/engine-name.xml:extensionID

fields.name: name
fields.description: The name of the default search engine.

fields.name: origin
fields.description: The origin of the search engine: the value will be default for engines that are built-in or from distribution partners, verified for user-installed engines with valid verification hashes, unverified for non-default engines without verification hash, and invalid for engines with broken verification hashes.

fields.name: submission_url
fields.description: The HTTP url we would use to search. For privacy, we don’t record this for user-installed engines.

fields.name: e10s_enabled
fields.description: True if the E10S is enabled.

fields.name: is_default_browser
fields.description: Identifier to indicate the particular link within a campaign.

fields.name: locale
fields.description: The best locale that the application should be localized to.

fields.name: effective_content_process_level
fields.description: The effective sandbox. The values are OS dependent.

fields.name: telemetry_enabled
fields.description: The state of the `toolkit.telemetry.enabled` pref.

fields.name: auto_download
fields.description: The state of the `app.update.auto` pref.

fields.name: channel
fields.description: The update channel from the defaults only. Does not include the partner bits.

fields.name: enabled
fields.description: The state of the `app.update.enabled` pref.

fields.name: cores
fields.description: The number of physical CPU cores. Desktop only, e.g. 4, or `null` on failure.

fields.name: count
fields.description: The number of logical CPUs. Desktop only, e.g. 8, or `null` on failure.

fields.name: family
fields.description: The CPU family, `null` on failure. Desktop only.

fields.name: l2cache_kb
fields.description: The CPU L2 cache size in KB. `null` on failure. Desktop only.

fields.name: l3cache_kb
fields.description: The CPU L3 cache size in KB. `null` on failure. Desktop only.

fields.name: model
fields.description: The CPU model, `null` on failure. Desktop only.

fields.name: speed_m_hz
fields.description: Only available on Firefox desktop. The CPU clock speed in MHz.

fields.name: stepping
fields.description: The CPU stepping, `null` on failure. Desktop only.

fields.name: vendor
fields.description: The CPU vendor, e.g. 'GenuineIntel', or `null` on failure. Desktop only.

fields.name: is_wow64
fields.description: The availability of the WoW64 subsystem. This is Windows only.

fields.name: memory_mb
fields.description: The machines amount of RAM.

fields.name: install_year
fields.description: The year Windows was installed. This is Windows only. `null` on failure.

fields.name: name
fields.description: The name of the OS, e.g. 'Windows_NT'. This is `null` on failure.

fields.name: service_pack_major
fields.description: The Windows service pack major version. This is Windows only. `null` on failure.

fields.name: service_pack_minor
fields.description: The Windows service pack minor version. This is Windows only. `null` on failure.

fields.name: version
fields.description: The version of the OS, e.g. '6.1'. This is `null` on failure.

fields.name: windows_build_number
fields.description: The Windows build number. This is Windows only. `null` on failure.

fields.name: windows_ubr
fields.description: The Windows UBR. This is Windows 10 only. `null` on failure.

country

fields.name: webrtc_nicer_stun_retransmits
fields.description: The count of STUN message retransmissions during a WebRTC call. When sending STUN request messages over UDP, messages may be dropped by the network. Retransmissions are the mechanism used to accomplish reliability of the STUN request/response transaction. This can happen during both successful and unsuccessful WebRTC calls. For more info on ICE, see https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5245 For more info on STUN, see https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5389 For more info on TURN, see https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5766

fields.name: webrtc_nicer_turn_401s
fields.description: The count of TURN 401 (Unauthorized) responses to allocation requests. Only 401 responses beyond the first, expected 401 are counted. More than one 401 repsonse indicates the client is experiencing difficulty authenticating with the TURN server. This can happen during both successful and unsuccessful WebRTC calls. For more info on ICE, see https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5245 For more info on STUN, see https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5389 For more info on TURN, see https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5766

fields.name: webrtc_nicer_turn_403s
fields.description: The count of TURN 403 (Forbidden) responses to CreatePermission or ChannelBind requests.  This indicates that the TURN server is refusing the request for an IP address or IP address/port combination, likely due to administrative restrictions. For more info on ICE, see https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5245 For more info on STUN, see https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5389 For more info on TURN, see https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5766

fields.name: webrtc_nicer_turn_438s
fields.description: The count of TURN 438 (Stale Nonce) responses to allocation requests. This can happen during both successful and unsuccessful WebRTC calls. For more info on ICE, see https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5245 For more info on STUN, see https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5389 For more info on TURN, see https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5766

fields.name: browser_engagement_active_ticks
fields.description: The count of the number of five-second intervals ('ticks') the user was considered 'active' in a subsession. Session activity involves keyboard or mouse interaction with the application. It does not take into account whether or not the window has focus or is in the foreground, only if it is receiving these interaction events.

fields.name: browser_engagement_max_concurrent_tab_count
fields.description: The count of maximum number of tabs open during a subsession, across all windows, including tabs in private windows and restored at startup.

fields.name: browser_engagement_max_concurrent_window_count
fields.description: The count of maximum number of browser windows open during a subsession. This includes private windows and the ones opened when starting the browser.

fields.name: browser_engagement_tab_open_event_count
fields.description: The count of tab open events per subsession, across all windows, after the session has been restored. This includes tab open events from private windows and from manual session restorations (i.e. after crashes and from about:home).

fields.name: browser_engagement_total_uri_count
fields.description: The count of the total non-unique http(s) URIs visited in a subsession, including page reloads, after the session has been restored. URIs on minimized or background tabs may also be counted towards this. Private browsing is not included in this count.

fields.name: browser_engagement_unfiltered_uri_count
fields.description: The count of the total non-unique URIs visited in a subsession, not restricted to a specific protocol, including page reloads and about:* pages (other than initial pages such as about:blank, ...), after the session has been restored. This does not include background page requests and URIs from embedded pages or private browsing.

fields.name: browser_engagement_unique_domains_count
fields.description: The count of the unique domains visited in a subsession, after the session has been restored. Subdomains under eTLD are aggregated after the first level (i.e. test.example.com and other.example.com are only counted once). This does not include background page requests and domains from embedded pages or private browsing. The count is limited to 100 unique domains.

fields.name: browser_engagement_window_open_event_count
fields.description: The count of browser window open events per subsession, after the session has been restored. The count includes private windows and the ones from manual session restorations (i.e. after crashes and from about:home).
